---
// AgentNative.astro — MCP server + AI assistant integration section
---

<section class="agent-native-section section-pad">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <span class="section-eyebrow" data-reveal>Agent-native</span>
    <h2 class="section-title" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="1">Built to be AI-native.</h2>
    <p class="section-desc" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="2">Kitaru ships an MCP server. Claude Code, Cursor, or any AI assistant can start flows, browse artifacts, and resume waiting agents — as naturally as running a shell command. Your tools already speak Kitaru.</p>

    <div class="an-grid" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="3">
      <!-- Left: conversation mockup -->
      <div class="conversation-window">
        <div class="conv-header">
          <span class="code-dot"></span><span class="code-dot"></span><span class="code-dot"></span>
          <span class="conv-title">Claude Code</span>
        </div>
        <div class="conv-body">
          <div class="conv-msg conv-user">
            <span class="conv-role">You</span>
            <span class="conv-text">Kick off 3 research agents on these topics: LLM routing, agent memory, tool selection</span>
          </div>
          <div class="conv-msg conv-assistant">
            <span class="conv-role">Assistant</span>
            <span class="conv-text">Started 3 flows: <code>kr-d41f</code> <code>kr-b82a</code> <code>kr-9c3e</code>. All running. <code>kr-d41f</code> is waiting — it found conflicting sources and needs guidance.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="conv-msg conv-user">
            <span class="conv-role">You</span>
            <span class="conv-text">Tell it to prioritize the 2024 benchmarks. What have the other two found so far?</span>
          </div>
          <div class="conv-msg conv-assistant">
            <span class="conv-role">Assistant</span>
            <span class="conv-text">Resumed <code>kr-d41f</code>. The other two have saved 12 artifacts — <code>kr-b82a</code> found 4 papers on retrieval-augmented memory, <code>kr-9c3e</code> is comparing 3 tool-selection frameworks.</span>
            <span class="conv-tool">kitaru_executions_input(exec_id="kr-d41f", wait="source_conflict", value="prioritize 2024 benchmarks")</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Right: what MCP gives you -->
      <div class="mcp-features">
        <h3>One CLI for the whole swarm</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <code>kitaru_executions_list</code>
            <span>Filter by status, flow, or stack</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <code>kitaru_executions_input</code>
            <span>Provide structured input to waiting flows</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <code>kitaru_executions_replay</code>
            <span>Replay from a checkpoint with overrides</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <code>kitaru_artifacts_get</code>
            <span>Browse outputs, prompts, and responses</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <div class="mcp-install">
          <code>pip install kitaru[mcp]</code>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .an-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.2fr 1fr;
    gap: 40px;
    align-items: start;
    margin-top: 48px;
  }

  /* Conversation mockup */
  .conversation-window {
    background: #1A1714;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    overflow: hidden;
    box-shadow: 0 8px 40px rgba(26,23,20,0.12);
  }

  .conv-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 12px 16px;
    gap: 8px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);
    background: rgba(26,23,20,0.95);
  }

  .conv-title {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.35);
    margin-left: 12px;
  }

  .conv-body {
    padding: 20px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 16px;
  }

  .conv-msg {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 4px;
  }

  .conv-role {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .conv-user .conv-role { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.35); }
  .conv-assistant .conv-role { color: var(--color-accent); }

  .conv-text {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #E8E4DE;
  }

  .conv-text code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    background: rgba(241,120,41,0.08);
    padding: 1px 5px;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }

  .conv-tool {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.25);
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 6px 10px;
    margin-top: 6px;
    word-break: break-all;
  }

  /* MCP features list */
  .mcp-features h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }

  .mcp-features ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 16px;
  }

  .mcp-features li {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2px;
  }

  .mcp-features li code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .mcp-features li span {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--color-secondary);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .mcp-install {
    margin-top: 24px;
    padding: 12px 16px;
    background: var(--color-surface-warm);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  .mcp-install code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .an-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 24px;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .conv-body { padding: 14px; }
    .conv-text { font-size: 0.78rem; }
    .conv-tool { font-size: 0.65rem; }
    .mcp-features li code { font-size: 0.78rem; }
    .mcp-features li span { font-size: 0.78rem; }
  }
</style>
